newspaper boy is a malayalam – language indian film released in 1955 . it is the first neo realistic movie in the language . the film , a drama of stark realism , narrates the life of the common man on the street . the film is noteworthy in that the entire production programme from script-writing to direction was controlled and executed by students . the group of students were from adarsh kalamandir and was written and directed by p. ramdas . the screenplay was based on a short story written by ramadas himself . though the film had a shoestring budget of ₹ 175,000 ( us$ 2,600 ) , featured mostly amateur actors , and was made by an inexperienced crew , newspaper boy was a critical success . influenced by italian neorealism , the film is also remembered for being the world 's first commercial film made by students .